text.tspan: Alice has used the wheel below to encrypt a sentence.
To help you find out how she used it to encrypt the text, she gave you
the first word of the decrypted version of the sentence.
Decrypt the rest of the sentence.
Drag letters from the wheel to the cells to form the decrypted sentence.
Click on the arrows to rotate the bottom row.
Easy version: simple substitution, all the user has to do
Medium version: no spaces, and after an initial arbitrary
shift, the wheel is shifted by one after decrypting each letter.
Hard version: after each letter, we shift either to the right or to
the left, depending on the letter (almost randomly). The user
needs to try both and determine which one corresponds to a
